Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s address for the latest information.

A State of Emergency was introduced on 19 March and renewed on 1 May to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19)in São Tomé and Príncipe. Social distancing measures are in place, all bars and restaurants are closed and gatherings of more than 10 people are prohibited.
For information on how to return to the UK from São Tomé and Príncipe, see Return to the UK.
Entry and borders
As part of the State of Emergency, entry to the country by all foreign travellers is prohibited until at least 16 May.
Nationals of São Tomé and Príncipe and foreign residents in the country will be subject to obligatory quarantine on return.
Charter flights and cruise ships are similarly prohibited.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
